# War Room — Cursor Context

## Product
Interview prep platform with two modes:
- Practice Mode (LeetCode/HackerRank style)
- Screening Mode (technical interview questions)
AI powered by Anthropic Claude
(claude-sonnet-4-20250514)

## Stack
- Frontend: React 19, Vite, TypeScript,
  vanilla CSS dark theme, JetBrains Mono
- Backend: Node.js, Express 4 (CommonJS)
- Database: SQLite via better-sqlite3,
  WAL mode
- AI: Anthropic Claude API,
  server-side proxy with cache-first
- Docker: multi-stage nginx build for
  client, Node Alpine for server

## Deployment
- Domain: https://warroom.codist.co.za
- Server: Hetzner VPS 65.109.7.45
- App dir: /opt/warroom
- App user: warroom
- Shared VPS with Billable
  (app.mybillable.co.za)
- Isolated: separate user, network,
  port from Billable

## Container layout (CRITICAL)
Server WORKDIR is /app NOT /app/server
  /app/index.js          entry point
  /app/controllers/      route handlers
  /app/middleware/       middleware
  /app/models/           SQLite models
  /app/routes/           route definitions
  /app/utils/            utilities
  /app/config/db.js      SQLite config
  /app/constants/        platform guides
  /app/data/warroom.db   SQLite database

Client: nginx build at 127.0.0.1:3080:80
  (prod override to avoid port 80 conflict
   with host nginx)

## Docker Compose
Base:    /opt/warroom/docker-compose.yml
Prod:    /opt/warroom/docker-compose.prod.yml
Start:   docker compose
           -f docker-compose.yml
           -f docker-compose.prod.yml
           up -d

## BusyBox grep (IMPORTANT)
Container uses BusyBox grep.
--include flag is NOT supported.
Use: grep -r "pattern" /app/dir/
NOT: grep -r "pattern" --include="*.js"

## Auth system
Files exist in repo and image:
  server/utils/appSession.js
  server/middleware/requireAppSession.js
  server/middleware/requireSuperUser.js
  server/controllers/authController.js
  server/controllers/guestUsersController.js
  client/src/components/AppAuthGate.tsx
  client/src/components/GuestPassesModal.tsx
  client/src/context/AuthSurfaceContext.tsx

Auth activated by env vars in
/opt/warroom/server/.env:
  WAR_ROOM_APP_USER=ntoko
  WAR_ROOM_APP_PASSWORD=<password>
  WAR_ROOM_SESSION_SECRET=<hex>
  COOKIE_SECURE=1

isAppAuthEnabled() checks if
WAR_ROOM_APP_USER is set.
If not set — app is open to anyone.
If set — sign-in screen enforced.

Super user can mint guest passes
(3hr expiry) via GUEST PASSES button
in header (only visible when logged
in as super user).

## CI/CD
Repo:    github.com/ntokyb/war-room
Branch:  main → auto deploys
Needs:   ci job must pass first
         deploy job blocked if ci fails

Deploy script on server:
  cd /opt/warroom
  git fetch origin main
  git reset --hard origin/main
  docker compose -f docker-compose.yml
    -f docker-compose.prod.yml
    build --no-cache
  docker compose -f docker-compose.yml
    -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
  docker image prune -f

## Environment
/opt/warroom/server/.env contains:
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
  PORT=5050
  WAR_ROOM_APP_USER
  WAR_ROOM_APP_PASSWORD
  WAR_ROOM_SESSION_SECRET
  COOKIE_SECURE=1

## Certifications tab
Added Apr 2026. Full roadmap:
AZ-900 → AZ-204 → AZ-400 →
AZ-104 → AZ-305 → TOGAF
30 AZ-900 flashcards built in.
localStorage persistence for
progress, mastery, exam dates.

## SQLite backup
Script: /home/billable/backup-warroom.sh
Runs: 2:30am daily via cron
Keeps: 14 days of backups

## Do not
- Edit production nginx by hand
  unless explicitly asked
- Modify Billable containers
  (separate app, separate user)
- Use --include flag with grep
  inside the container
- Run migrations inside the container
  (no .NET SDK — runtime only)
